title: Bug 109350 - Output parameter does not display in data set dialog
description: The output parameter is not being displayed in the data set dialog.
OB: Currently, the output parameter is not visible in the data set dialog when calling a stored procedure from an Oracle database and storing the query result in the output parameter as an object. There is no data returned in the query result page.
EB: The output parameter should be displayed in the data set dialog when calling a stored procedure from an Oracle database and storing the query result in the output parameter as an object. The query result page should show the data in the output parameter.
SR:
Steps to reproduce:
1. Call a stored procedure from an Oracle database
2. Store the query result in the output parameter as an object
3. Open the data set dialog

Expected result:
- The output parameter is visible in the data set dialog
- The query result page shows the data in the output parameter.
